{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/blog/2018/add-dangerjs-to-your-project","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"what-is-dangerjs-anyway\" style=\"position:relative;\">What is danger.js anyway?<a href=\"#what-is-dangerjs-anyway\" aria-label=\"what is dangerjs anyway permalink\" class=\"blog-post-heading-link after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://danger.systems/js/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">DangerJS</a> runs during your CI process, and helps your team to automate certain manual code review tasks like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Is there a <code class=\"language-text\">new library</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">module installed</code>?</li>\n<li>Does this <code class=\"language-text\">PR changes</code> are added to <code class=\"language-text\">changelog file</code>?</li>\n<li>Is <code class=\"language-text\">.lockfile</code> kept up to date?</li>\n<li>Will this change <code class=\"language-text\">increase my bundle size</code>?</li>\n<li>So on and on.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-20\">Example:</b></p>\n<center>\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 700px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 39.42857142857142%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"DangerJS in React\" title=\"DangerJS in React\" src=\"/static/15ff828df33fb814c34268d983dcd6e5/8c557/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695.png\" srcset=\"/static/15ff828df33fb814c34268d983dcd6e5/4edbd/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695.png 175w,\n/static/15ff828df33fb814c34268d983dcd6e5/13ae7/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695.png 350w,\n/static/15ff828df33fb814c34268d983dcd6e5/8c557/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695.png 700w,\n/static/15ff828df33fb814c34268d983dcd6e5/e996b/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695.png 1050w,\n/static/15ff828df33fb814c34268d983dcd6e5/2cefc/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695.png 1400w,\n/static/15ff828df33fb814c34268d983dcd6e5/d61c2/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695.png 1800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n  <i class=\"m-top-15\">React using danger.js</i>\n</center>\n<h4>Integrating Danger.js in Github &#x26; Travis</h4>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-10 m-top-10\">Step 1:</b> Add <code class=\"language-text\">dangerjs</code> to <code class=\"language-text\">your devDependencies</code> in package.json file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token function\">yarn</span> <span class=\"token function\">add</span> danger -D</code></pre></div>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-10 m-top-10\">Step 2:</b> Create <code class=\"language-text\">dangerfile.js</code> file in your project.</p>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-20\">Example:</b></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Import the feedback functions</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> message<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> warn<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> fail<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> markdown <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'danger'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Add a message to the table</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">message</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'You have added 2 more modules to the app'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">//  Adds a warning to the table</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">warn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'You have not included a CHANGELOG entry.'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Declares a blocking</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">fail</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">ESLint has failed with </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>fails<span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\"> fails.</span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Show markdown under the table:</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">markdown</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'## New module Danger'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> dangerYarnInfo<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-10 m-top-10\">Step 3 (Optional):</b> Create an <code class=\"language-text\">github account</code> for <code class=\"language-text\">your bot</code>.</p>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-10 m-top-10\">Step 4:</b> Create a <a href=\"https://github.com/settings/tokens/new\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">New personal access token</a> in <code class=\"language-text\">github</code> for <code class=\"language-text\">read &amp; write</code> access for your bot.</p>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-20\">Example:</b></p>\n<center>\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 700px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 57.14285714285714%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Github Settings Page\" title=\"Github Settings Page\" src=\"/static/6b0e8af6636a1e8456a0df0c357e1cbc/8c557/github-token.png\" srcset=\"/static/6b0e8af6636a1e8456a0df0c357e1cbc/4edbd/github-token.png 175w,\n/static/6b0e8af6636a1e8456a0df0c357e1cbc/13ae7/github-token.png 350w,\n/static/6b0e8af6636a1e8456a0df0c357e1cbc/8c557/github-token.png 700w,\n/static/6b0e8af6636a1e8456a0df0c357e1cbc/e996b/github-token.png 1050w,\n/static/6b0e8af6636a1e8456a0df0c357e1cbc/2cefc/github-token.png 1400w,\n/static/6b0e8af6636a1e8456a0df0c357e1cbc/0f586/github-token.png 1498w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n  <i class=\"m-top-15\">Github Settings Page</i>\n</center>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-10 m-top-10\">Step 5 (Final Step):</b> <code class=\"language-text\">Hooking danger.js</code> in <a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Travis CI</a></p>\n<ul class=\"m-left-10\">\n  <li>Copy the <b>generated personal token</b> from your github or your bot account you created.</li>\n  <li>Go to your <b>project settings</b> in <b>Travis CI</b>.</li>\n  <li>Create a <b>new environment variable</b> called <b>DANGER_GITHUB_API_TOKEN</b> and the value is <b>your personal token</b>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-20\">Example:</b></p>\n<center>\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 700px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 49.71428571428571%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Travis Settings Page\" title=\"Travis Settings Page\" src=\"/static/5d1c9cd4444590a3cdca6e8e97e6dda0/8c557/travis-ci.org.png\" srcset=\"/static/5d1c9cd4444590a3cdca6e8e97e6dda0/4edbd/travis-ci.org.png 175w,\n/static/5d1c9cd4444590a3cdca6e8e97e6dda0/13ae7/travis-ci.org.png 350w,\n/static/5d1c9cd4444590a3cdca6e8e97e6dda0/8c557/travis-ci.org.png 700w,\n/static/5d1c9cd4444590a3cdca6e8e97e6dda0/e996b/travis-ci.org.png 1050w,\n/static/5d1c9cd4444590a3cdca6e8e97e6dda0/2cefc/travis-ci.org.png 1400w,\n/static/5d1c9cd4444590a3cdca6e8e97e6dda0/d0ab7/travis-ci.org.png 1532w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n  <i class=\"m-top-15\">Travis Settings Page</i>\n</center>\n<p>After this step, you should be seeing <code class=\"language-text\">bot</code> account adding <code class=\"language-text\">comments</code> to your every PR as per your <code class=\"language-text\">dangerfile.js</code> config.</p>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-20\">Example:</b> <a href=\"https://github.com/code-kotis/barcode-scanner/pull/57\" target=\"_blank\">QR Code Scanner</a></p>\n<center>\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 700px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 105.14285714285714%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Code Kotis - QR Code Scanner\" title=\"Code Kotis - QR Code Scanner\" src=\"/static/1ad59b1ba922871d233e8003cc7f3eef/8c557/github.com_code-kotis.png\" srcset=\"/static/1ad59b1ba922871d233e8003cc7f3eef/4edbd/github.com_code-kotis.png 175w,\n/static/1ad59b1ba922871d233e8003cc7f3eef/13ae7/github.com_code-kotis.png 350w,\n/static/1ad59b1ba922871d233e8003cc7f3eef/8c557/github.com_code-kotis.png 700w,\n/static/1ad59b1ba922871d233e8003cc7f3eef/e996b/github.com_code-kotis.png 1050w,\n/static/1ad59b1ba922871d233e8003cc7f3eef/2cefc/github.com_code-kotis.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n  <i class=\"m-top-15\"><a href=\"qrcodescan.in\" target=\"_blank\">QR Code Scanner</a></i>\n</center>\n<h5>Hot Tips:</h5>\n<p>You can test your changes locally using following terminal command.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token function\">yarn</span> danger <span class=\"token function\">pr</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>your-pr-link<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h5>References:</h5>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/facebook/react/pull/11865/files\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">ReactJS</a> dangerfile.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://danger.systems/js/tutorials.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Tutorials</a> for other app such as node app, node libraries etc.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://danger.systems/js/guides/getting_started.html#setting-up-danger-to-run-on-your-ci\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">More tutorials</a> on adding danger.js to other CI's</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Thank you for reading my post till the end. If you like my post <code class=\"language-text\">share it</code> ðŸ˜‡.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"Oct 16, 2018","updated":null,"slug":"/blog/2018/add-dangerjs-to-your-project","title":"Add danger.js to your OSS in 5 mins","description":null,"relative":null},"fields":{"readingTime":{"text":"2 min read"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2018/add-dangerjs-to-your-project"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3633477710"]}